                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="85045" author="masrawi" created="Tue, 13 Nov 2012 02:46:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am using in web.xml&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;listener&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;listener-class&amp;gt;org.springframework.web.util.Log4jConfigListener&amp;lt;/listener-class&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/listener&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="88357" author="grussell" created="Thu, 28 Feb 2013 14:32:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You can get a &lt;tt&gt;main()&lt;/tt&gt; to terminate by adding &lt;tt&gt;Log4jConfigurer.shutdownLogging();&lt;/tt&gt; at the end (or preferably in a finally block).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;log-event-retry-delay&lt;/tt&gt; thread still remains, but the connection factory is destroyed (it&apos;s the rabbit threads that prevent the JVM from terminating).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;log-event-retry-delay&lt;/tt&gt; thread is a daemon so it won&apos;t hold up a &lt;tt&gt;main&lt;/tt&gt; from exiting (but it still causes the tomcat message).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can avoid this by adding &lt;tt&gt;retryTimer.cancel();&lt;/tt&gt; to the &lt;tt&gt;close()&lt;/tt&gt; method in the &lt;tt&gt;AmqpAppender&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="88364" author="grussell" created="Thu, 28 Feb 2013 19:51:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;PR: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/SpringSource/spring-amqp/pull/81&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/SpringSource/spring-amqp/pull/81&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
